# Product north star

**Sheetomatic = EM Ready owner operations platform** for BCI/CEOITBOX-style Indian SMEs.

**USP:** FMS, IMS, tasks, checklists, and MIS auto-update all week. Owner/reviewer opens the system and **starts EM with zero prep** — no MIS hire needed to compile reports.

When designing UI, APIs, or prioritizing work, ask: *Does this make EM Ready faster? Does person-wise KRA/KPI show deficits clearly?*

## Core product (build and invest here)

### EM Ready (hero outcome)
- One owner/reviewer view for weekly executive meeting (EM)
- Auto-fetched, live data — no human prepares slides or merges Sheets before the meeting
- Exceptions-first: overdue, delayed, pending, stock breaches — not raw row dumps

### FMS — Flow Management System (multiple allowed)
- An org can have **multiple FMS templates** (split FMS): e.g. Order Placed, Sample, Dispatch, Payment follow-up
- Each FMS defines steps with Who / How / When / proof channel / SLA
- Per job/instance: Planned | Actual | Status | Time Delay per step
- SLA breach drives internal WhatsApp alerts (staff only — not customer chatbot)

### IMS — Inventory Management System
- Stock in/out, balances, reorder exceptions
- Feeds same person-wise KRA/KPI and EM board as FMS

### Task delegation, checklists, PMS/MIS
- Tasks, recurring checklists, and other modules feed the **same EM scoreboard**
- All roll up to **person-wise KRA/KPI** on EM

### WhatsApp role
- **Internal alerts only** — task assign, SLA breach, overdue nudges
- Official API first; Web Based API dev-only unless `NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_WEB_BASED_API=true`
- Not a JoyzAI-style customer FAQ bot (deprioritize)

### Native forms — no Google Forms, no Sheet formulas
- **Do not** depend on Google Forms, prefilled Form URLs, IMPORTRANGE, or BMP-style Sheet formulas for FMS/PC/HR capture
- **Sheetomatic builds the forms** — step completion, checklist runs, HR screening, PO lines, etc. are in-app (web; WA deep links later if needed)
- SLA (planned/actual/delay), DB_Format unpivot, For PC, and conditional RAG run in **server TypeScript + Postgres**, not Sheets
- Google Sheets/Looker may remain optional **export or mirror** for owners who want a spreadsheet view — not the runtime

## KRA/KPI scoring — deficit (negative) framing

**Critical:** Person-wise KRA/KPI is shown as **negative deficit %**, NOT positive “% done”.

### Do NOT show
- “8 of 10 done = 80%” completion framing on EM/KRA views

### DO show
- Penalty-style deficit from gaps and delays
- Example: 10 tasks assigned, **2 still pending** → show **-20%**, not 80% done
- Each unit (task, FMS step, checklist item, etc.) contributes `-100 / total_count` per violation category unless a module-specific weight is defined

### Example task breakdown (10 tasks)
| Status | Count | EM meaning |
|--------|-------|------------|
| Done on time | 2 | No penalty |
| Not done on time (open, past due) | 6 | Penalty each |
| Pending and delayed | 1 | Penalty (pending + delay) |
| Done but delayed | 1 | Penalty (late completion) |

Person KRA/KPI = sum of penalties across **all modules** (tasks + all FMS instances + IMS exceptions + checklists) for that person in the EM period.

### Violation categories (default weights — tune per module)
1. **Pending** (not started / still open) — full unit penalty `-100/total`
2. **Overdue open** (not done on time) — full unit penalty
3. **Done late** (completed after SLA) — penalty (same or reduced weight per product decision)
4. **On time** — zero penalty

Display: person row shows e.g. **Tasks -20% | FMS Order Flow -15% | Checklist -10% | Total -45%** (or single rolled-up deficit — UI TBD).

